```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "proc",
    "account": "EAR21003",
    "nodes": 20,
    "tasks_per_node": 56,
    "time": "00:20:00",
    "partition": "normal",
    "environment": {
      "conda": "py3",
      "UCX_TLS": "knem,dc_x"
    },
    "scripts": [
      "generate_path_files.py",
      "proc.py",
      "run_mpi_queue.py"
    ],
    "files": [
      "paths.yml",
      "settings.yml",
      "event_list",
      "parfile/proc_obsd_1D_crust.{p}.param.yml",
      "paths/proc_obsd_1D_crust.{e}.{p}.path.json",
      "jobs_proc_obsd_1D_crust_{SLURM_JOBID}"
    ]
  }
}
```

The script is running on a SLURM cluster, submitting a job named "proc" to the "normal" partition. It requests 20 nodes with 56 tasks per node, running for a maximum of 20 minutes. The script activates the conda environment "py3", uses the Python scripts "generate_path_files.py" and "proc.py" and runs the MPI job using "run_mpi_queue.py". It also reads configuration files "paths.yml" and "settings.yml" and a list of events from "event_list". The script generates a job file named "jobs_proc_obsd_1D_crust_{SLURM_JOBID}". The script uses the environment variable "UCX_TLS" to configure the communication protocol for MPI.
